# WalletPulse Project Context

## What is WalletPulse?

An Android-only, offline-first, multi-currency expense tracker built with React Native. It captures push notifications from financial apps (Payoneer, Grey, Dukascopy Bank), parses transaction details through regex, and logs expenses to a local WatermelonDB database with real-time currency conversion. Designed to compete with top expense trackers through speed, functionality, and a polished enterprise-grade UI.

## Development Philosophy

- **Test-Driven Development (TDD)**: Write failing tests first, then implementation, then refactor
- **Clean Architecture**: Domain, Data, Presentation, and Infrastructure layers with strict dependency rules
- **Enterprise UI**: Human-centered design with micro-interactions, skeleton loading, haptic feedback, and accessibility
- **Offline-First**: Every feature works without internet; sync when available
- **No em dashes**: Never use the "--" (em dash) character in any text, comments, UI strings, or documentation

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React Native 0.76+ (bare workflow, no Expo) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) |
| Database | WatermelonDB with SQLiteAdapter (JSI enabled) |
| State | Zustand for UI state, WatermelonDB observables for data |
| Navigation | React Navigation 7 (bottom tabs + native stack) |
| Charts | react-native-gifted-charts |
| Styling | React Native StyleSheet + design token system |
| Notifications | Android NotificationListenerService (native module) |
| FX Rates | ExchangeRate-API (free tier) with local caching |
| Security | react-native-keychain, optional SQLCipher encryption |
| Testing | Jest + @testing-library/react-native (TDD) |
| Animations | react-native-reanimated 3 |

## Clean Architecture Structure

```
src/
├── domain/                    # Pure business logic (no framework imports)
│   ├── entities/              # Core business objects
│   ├── repositories/          # Repository interfaces (ports)
│   ├── usecases/              # Application business rules
│   └── value-objects/         # Immutable value types (Money, Currency)
├── data/                      # Data layer (implements domain interfaces)
│   ├── database/              # WatermelonDB schema, models, migrations
│   ├── repositories/          # Repository implementations (adapters)
│   ├── datasources/           # Local DB + remote API data sources
│   └── mappers/               # Entity to/from DB model mappers
├── presentation/              # UI layer
│   ├── screens/               # Full screen components
│   ├── components/            # Reusable UI components
│   │   ├── common/            # Buttons, inputs, cards, modals
│   │   ├── charts/            # Chart wrapper components
│   │   ├── feedback/          # Skeleton, empty state, error state
│   │   └── layout/            # Headers, footers, containers
│   ├── navigation/            # React Navigation setup and types
│   ├── stores/                # Zustand stores (presentation state)
│   └── hooks/                 # UI-specific hooks
├── infrastructure/            # External services and platform code
│   ├── notification/          # Android notification listener + parsers
│   ├── currency/              # FX rate API client
│   ├── export/                # CSV, Excel, PDF generators
│   ├── backup/                # Local and cloud backup
│   └── native/                # Native module JS bridges
├── shared/                    # Cross-cutting concerns
│   ├── theme/                 # Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing)
│   ├── types/                 # Shared TypeScript types
│   ├── utils/                 # Pure utility functions
│   └── constants/             # App-wide constants
└── __tests__/                 # Mirrors src/ structure
```

## Dependency Rule

```
Presentation --> Domain <-- Data
                   ^
                   |
             Infrastructure
```

Domain layer has ZERO imports from any other layer. Data and Infrastructure depend on Domain. Presentation depends on Domain and receives data through hooks/stores.

## Key Conventions

- All financial amounts stored as integers (cents) to avoid float rounding
- Dates stored as Unix timestamps (milliseconds)
- Currency codes follow ISO 4217 (USD, EUR, GBP, ETB)
- Every database model has `created_at` and `updated_at` fields
- Notification parsers are pure functions: `(notification) => ParsedTransaction | null`
- Components use named exports, screens use default exports
- File naming: `kebab-case.ts` for logic, `PascalCase.tsx` for components
- Every new module starts with a test file (TDD red-green-refactor)
- Never use em dash characters anywhere in the codebase
